item.title: Need some help removing the cart in edgeville. in 317
item.dc:creator: @pure2ownage Pure_
item.description:
@pure2ownage wrote:

[quote=“eballer48, post:3, topic:342099”][quote author=pure2ownage link=topic=438510.msg3222752#msg3222752 date=1275312891]
public void Deleteobjects() {
[/quote]
you have to bee more specific he’s a learner…
okay so go on your server and type ::noclip (if you dont have it fixed) (if you do then unfix it for a sec) then walk on the spot where the cart is… type ::mypos and get the cords.
then go to client.java and search for public void Deleteobjects()
there should be a long list just go down to the bottom of the list and type the following…

 	       deletethatobject(3509, 9497);

CODE BREAK DOWN:

 	       deletethatobject

Pretty simple delete that object… now other sources it make something diffrent but the word delete should be in there…

 	       (3509, 9497);

The cords of an object.
So all in all heres your code:

deletethatobject(XCORD, YCORD); [/quote]
Here at moparscape we do not spoon feed.
